title: Comparing the prevalence of condylomata acuminata between pregnant women and nonpregnant controls in South Korea: a population-based, cross-sectional study.
abstract: We analyzed and estimated the prevalence of condylomata acuminata from South Korea claim data in 2009. The prevalence in pregnant women aged 20 to 34 years (46 ± 7 per 100,000 persons) was lower than that in nonpregnant women aged 20 to 34 years (59 ± 1 per 100,000 persons; P < 0.001).
